message: The 33-year-old quit her well-paying job at the prestigious Procopio law firm in downtown San Diego to start a nonprofit that will take on the legal messes of trafficked victims. “I’m hearing over and over again, ‘I’ve never had a lawyer before.’ ‘The only lawyer I’ve had was a public defender when I was charged with a crime,’” Quient said in an interview this week.

data.description: Jamie Quient quit her well-paying job at the prestigious Procopio law firm in downtown San Diego to start Free to Thrive, a nonprofit that will take on the legal messes of trafficked victims.
data.title: Human trafficking survivors get a highly qualified legal advocate
